localization.en: Tap or Drag cards in the game area to move them to a new valid position.
localization.fr: Triez les cartes dans la zone de jeu principale (appelée tableau). Les cartes se retourneront automatiquement si une carte en est retirée. Les cartes peuvent être tapées ou glissées et ne peuvent être placées les unes sur les autres que par ordre décroissant avec des couleurs alternées (rouge et noir).
localization.esp: Clasifica cartas en el área principal del juego (llamada tablero). Las tarjetas se voltearán automáticamente si se quita una tarjeta de ellas. Las tarjetas se pueden tocar o arrastrar y solo se pueden colocar una encima de la otra en orden descendente con colores alternos (rojo y negro).

localization.en: Cards can be placed on top of each other in decending order with alternating colors (Red & Black). Cards will automatically flip over if a card is moved off of them.
localization.fr: Lorsque les cartes sont empilées les unes sur les autres, la pile entière ou seulement une partie de la pile peut être déplacée en appuyant ou en saisissant la carte que vous souhaitez déplacer (toutes les cartes sous la carte sélectionnée se déplaceront en même temps).
localization.esp: Cuando las cartas se apilan una encima de la otra, se puede mover toda la pila o solo una parte de la pila tocando o agarrando la carta que desea mover (todas las cartas debajo de la carta seleccionada se moverán al mismo tiempo).

localization.en: You can move an ace up to one of the empty slots to start build the foundation.
localization.fr: Voici 4 pieux de fondation. Pour construire un pieu de fondation, un As doit d’abord être placé dans l’un des emplacements. Les cartes de la même couleur peuvent être placées au-dessus de l'As dans l'ordre de l'As au Roi. Complétez les 4 piles et gagnez !
localization.esp: Aquí hay 4 pilotes de cimentación. Para construir una pila de cimientos, primero se debe colocar un As en una de las ranuras. Las cartas del mismo palo se pueden colocar encima del As en orden del As al Rey. ¡Completa las 4 pilas y gana!

localization.en: Move cards up to the top by placing cards in acending order. If you can move all of the cards to the foundation, you win!
You can move a Kings to any empty column to start a new stack and help bring more cards into play.
localization.fr: Déplacer les rois dans des colonnes vides

localization.en: Tapping on the top of the stock pile (the extra cards) will flip to reveal the next card in the deck. Once all of the cards are flipped over from the stock pile, it can be reset by tapping again.
localization.fr: En appuyant sur le haut de la pile (les cartes supplémentaires), vous retournerez la carte suivante du jeu. Déplacez les cartes de la zone de la réserve vers la fondation ou vers le tableau. Une fois que toutes les cartes de la pile sont retournées, elles peuvent être réinitialisées en appuyant sur.
localization.esp: Al tocar la parte superior de la pila (las cartas adicionales), se volteará para revelar la siguiente carta del mazo. Mueva las cartas del área de la pila de valores a la base o al cuadro. Una vez que se dan la vuelta a todas las cartas de la pila, se pueden restablecer tocando.

localization.en: Move cards from the stock pile to either the tableau below or directly to the fountation to the left.
localization.fr: SUPER! MAINTENANT VOUS CONNAISSEZ LES BASES.

localization.en: Sometimes to get to the card you need, you will have to move cards around in the bottom area. Try moving the 3 of Spades to the 4 of Diamonds.
localization.fr: SUPER! MAINTENANT VOUS CONNAISSEZ LES BASES.

localization.en: Now you have access to the 4 of Hearts so you can move it up to the fountation.
localization.fr: SUPER! MAINTENANT VOUS CONNAISSEZ LES BASES.

localization.en: At any point if you have remaining stock pile cards, you can continue to flip the pile to see if you can bring new cards into play.
localization.fr: SUPER! MAINTENANT VOUS CONNAISSEZ LES BASES.

localization.en: Moving Cards Back to the Tableau
You can drag cards from the foundation back to the game area below to help bring more cards into play. Try dragging the 4 of Hearts to the 5 of clubs.
localization.fr: SUPER! MAINTENANT VOUS CONNAISSEZ LES BASES.

localization.en: Moving Cards Back to the Tableau
Now that the 4 of Hearts is back in the tabeau, you can bring the 3 of Clubs down into the game area.
localization.fr: SUPER! MAINTENANT VOUS CONNAISSEZ LES BASES.

localization.en: Now that the 4 of Hearts is back in the tabeau, you can bring the 3 of Clubs down into the game area.
localization.fr: SUPER! MAINTENANT VOUS CONNAISSEZ LES BASES.

localization.en: Q: Why are there ads and can I turn them off?
localization.fr: Q : Pourquoi y a-t-il des publicités et puis-je les désactiver ?

localization.en: Please consider that this game is free to download. Advertising revenue allows our small development team to address feedback and to evolve the product over time to provide a great experience for our players.
localization.fr: Veuillez considérer que ce jeu est téléchargeable gratuitement. Les revenus publicitaires permettent à notre petite équipe de développement de répondre aux commentaires et de faire évoluer le produit au fil du temps afin d'offrir une expérience exceptionnelle à nos joueurs.
localization.esp: Tenga en cuenta que este juego se puede descargar gratis. Los ingresos por publicidad permiten a nuestro pequeño equipo de desarrollo abordar los comentarios y hacer evolucionar el producto con el tiempo para brindar una gran experiencia a nuestros jugadores.

localization.en: You can turn off advertising when you upgrade the game to Premium (accessed through the options menu “Remove Ads”). This will remove ads for the duration of your subscription.
localization.fr: Vous pouvez désactiver la publicité lorsque vous mettez à niveau le jeu vers Premium (accessible via le menu d'options « Supprimer les publicités »). Cela supprimera les publicités pour la durée de votre abonnement.
localization.esp: Puedes desactivar la publicidad cuando actualizas el juego a Premium (al que se accede a través del menú de opciones Eliminar anuncios). Esto eliminará los anuncios mientras dure su suscripción.

localization.en: If you would like to report a specific issue with an ad that is being served to you, please use the feedback link in the options menu email and send us an image of the ad along with a description of the situation and we will try to help resolve this for you.
localization.fr: Si vous souhaitez signaler un problème spécifique avec une annonce qui vous est diffusée, veuillez utiliser le lien de commentaires dans l'e-mail du menu d'options et envoyez-nous une image de l'annonce ainsi qu'une description de la situation et nous essaierons de vous aider. résolvez cela pour vous.
localization.esp: Si desea informar un problema específico con un anuncio que se le muestra, utilice el enlace de comentarios en el correo electrónico del menú de opciones y envíenos una imagen del anuncio junto con una descripción de la situación e intentaremos ayudarlo. resuelve esto por ti.

localization.en: Q: What's the difference between Classic Scoring and Vegas Scoring?
localization.fr: Q : Quelle est la différence entre le score classique et le score Vegas ?
localization.esp: P: ¿Cuál es la diferencia entre la puntuación clásica y la puntuación Vegas?

localization.en: A: Essentially, Classic Scoring uses a scoring table that earns you points based on how many cards are flipped over and moved to the foundation in a certain amount of time whereas Vegas Scoring will turn your score into $ dollars where you earn $ for moving cards to the foundation.
localization.fr: R : Essentiellement, Classic Scoring utilise un tableau de notation qui vous rapporte des points en fonction du nombre de cartes retournées et déplacées vers la fondation dans un certain laps de temps, tandis que Vegas Scoring transformera votre score en dollars et vous gagnerez des dollars pour le déplacement des cartes. à la fondation.
localization.esp: R: Básicamente, Classic Scoring utiliza una tabla de puntuación que le otorga puntos en función de cuántas cartas se voltean y se mueven a la base en un cierto período de tiempo, mientras que Vegas Scoring convertirá su puntuación en $ dólares, donde usted ganará $ por mover las cartas. a la fundación.

localization.en: Q: Can I change the designs of the cards or background?
localization.fr: Q : Puis-je modifier le design des cartes ou de l'arrière-plan ?
localization.esp: P: ¿Puedo cambiar los diseños de las tarjetas o el fondo?

localization.en: A: Yes! You can change the look of the game by modifying the Visual Themes.
localization.fr: R : Oui ! Vous pouvez changer l'apparence du jeu en modifiant les thèmes visuels.
localization.esp: R: ¡Sí! Puedes cambiar el aspecto del juego modificando los temas visuales.

localization.en: Q: How do I change the Card Designs & Game Backgrounds?
localization.fr: Q : Comment puis-je modifier les modèles de cartes et les arrière-plans du jeu ?
localization.esp: P: ¿Cómo cambio los diseños de las cartas y los fondos del juego?

localization.en: A: To change the card design or the background, tap the themes button in the bottom navigation when you are inside a Solitaire and scroll to “Customization” and select the desired option. Some themes are automatically unlocked while others require coins to unlock. Coins can be earned through winning the solitaire games or with a premium upgrade.
localization.fr: R : Pour modifier le design de la carte ou l'arrière-plan, appuyez sur Paramètres, faites défiler jusqu'à « Personnalisation » et sélectionnez l'option souhaitée. Certains thèmes sont automatiquement déverrouillés tandis que d'autres nécessitent des pièces pour être déverrouillés. Les pièces peuvent être gagnées en remportant les jeux de solitaire ou avec une mise à niveau premium.
localization.esp: R: Para cambiar el diseño de la tarjeta o el fondo, toque configuración, desplácese hasta Personalización y seleccione la opción deseada. Algunos temas se desbloquean automáticamente mientras que otros requieren monedas para desbloquearse. Las monedas se pueden ganar ganando los juegos de solitario o con una mejora premium.

localization.en: Q: How do I earn Coins When Winning a Game?
localization.fr: Q : Comment puis-je gagner des pièces en gagnant un jeu ?
localization.esp: P: ¿Cómo gano monedas al ganar un juego?

localization.en: A: After winning a Solitaire game you are awarded coins that can be used to unlock various visual themes in the settings area.
localization.fr: R : Après avoir remporté une partie de Solitaire, vous recevez des pièces qui peuvent être utilisées pour débloquer divers thèmes visuels dans la zone des paramètres.
localization.esp: R: Después de ganar un juego de Solitario, recibirás monedas que podrás usar para desbloquear varios temas visuales en el área de configuración.

localization.en: Winning Standard 1 Card Solitaire +50 Coins|Winning Standard 3 Card Solitaire +100 Coins|Winning Vegas 1 Card Solitaire +150 Coins|Winning Vegas 3 Card Solitaire +200 Coins
localization.fr: Solitaire gagnant à 1 carte standard + 50 pièces | Solitaire gagnant à 3 cartes standard + 100 pièces | Solitaire gagnant à 1 carte Vegas + 150 pièces | Solitaire gagnant à 3 cartes Vegas + 200 pièces
localization.esp: Solitario estándar ganador de 1 carta +50 monedas|Solitario estándar ganador de 3 cartas +100 monedas|Solitario ganador de 1 carta Vegas +150 monedas|Solitario ganador de 3 cartas Vegas +200 monedas

localization.fr: Q : Que sont les défis quotidiens ?

localization.en: A: Each day, a new challenge is available to play (each challenge is winnable). Winning the challenge will move your progress forward and once you reach various thresholds, you will be awarded special prizes. The game format follows the Standard Solitaire 1 Card format but you can only win once a day (the challenge will reset to the following day’s challenge once the red timer finishes counting down). If you complete a challenge, you are able to share that score with your friend to see if they can beat you. You can access the daily challenges when you click the New Shuffle button in the bottom navigation.
localization.fr: R : Chaque jour, un nouveau défi est disponible (chaque défi peut être gagné). Gagner le défi fera avancer votre progression et une fois que vous aurez atteint différents seuils, vous recevrez des prix spéciaux. Le format du jeu suit le format Standard Solitaire 1 Card mais vous ne pouvez gagner qu'une fois par jour (le défi sera réinitialisé au défi du lendemain une fois le compte à rebours terminé par le chronomètre rouge). Si vous terminez un défi, vous pouvez partager ce score avec votre ami pour voir s'il peut vous battre.
localization.esp: R: Cada día, hay un nuevo desafío disponible para jugar (cada desafío se puede ganar). Ganar el desafío hará avanzar tu progreso y, una vez que alcances varios umbrales, recibirás premios especiales. El formato del juego sigue el formato de Solitario estándar de 1 carta, pero solo puedes ganar una vez al día (el desafío se restablecerá al desafío del día siguiente una vez que el cronómetro rojo termine la cuenta regresiva). Si completas un desafío, podrás compartir esa puntuación con tu amigo para ver si puede vencerte.

localization.en: Q: How can I see myself on the Leaderboards?
localization.fr: Q : Comment puis-je me voir dans les classements ?
localization.esp: P: ¿Cómo puedo verme en las tablas de clasificación?

localization.en: A: To access the leaderboards, you must sign in to Game Center on your device (either by clicking “Sign In” on the Leaderboards view or the Achievements View (accessed through the Options screen or through the New Shuffle button during a game). Once you login to Game Center you will be able to see how you rank vs. other players who are also logged in through the Game Center system.
localization.fr: R : Pour accéder aux classements, vous devez vous connecter à Game Center sur votre appareil (soit en cliquant sur Connexion dans la vue Classements, soit dans la vue Réalisations (accessible via le menu d'options). Une fois connecté à Game Center, vous serez capable de voir votre classement par rapport aux autres joueurs également connectés via le système Game Center.
localization.esp: R: Para acceder a las tablas de clasificación, debes iniciar sesión en Game Center en tu dispositivo (ya sea haciendo clic en Iniciar sesión en la vista de Tablas de clasificación o en la Vista de logros (a la que se accede a través del menú de opciones). Una vez que inicies sesión en Game Center, serás Podrás ver tu clasificación frente a otros jugadores que también hayan iniciado sesión a través del sistema Game Center.

localization.en: Thanks, we hope you enjoy our game!
Looks like you're a pro! Make sure to try the other game modes like Vegas Solitaire that can be accessed through the Options menu.
localization.fr: On dirait que tu es un pro ! Assurez-vous d'essayer les autres modes de jeu comme Vegas Solitaire, accessibles via le menu Options.
localization.esp: ¡Parece que eres un profesional! Asegúrate de probar otros modos de juego como Vegas Solitaire a los que se puede acceder a través del menú Opciones.

localization.esp: Estás jugando a Vegas Scoring. Sólo se le permite revisar la pila de existencias un número limitado de veces.

localization.en: Classic Solitaire uses a standard 52 card deck of playing cards (without jokers).

The objective of the game is to reveal and sort cards in the main game area (called the tableau) and move them up into the foundation piles (4 boxes with an “A” inside). Once all cards are moved to the foundation, you win!
A. Foundation|B. Tableau|C. Scoring|D. Stock Pile|E. Main Navigation

There are 4 foundation piles (each of the 4 piles indicated by a box with an “A” inside). To begin building a foundation pile, an Ace must be placed in one of the slots. Cards of the same suit can be placed on top of the Ace in order from Ace to King. Once all 4 foundation piles are built up, the game is over.

The game begins with a cascading arrangement of cards (randomly dealt) being placed in the 7 tableau columns face down with the top card in each column revealed. Card sequences can be built by placing cards in descending values (e.g., J, 10, 9, 8, etc.) and in alternating colors (Red, Black) on top of each other. Within the tableau area, sequences of cards or partially completed piles can be moved on top of other cards in other columns as long as it will continue the descending card sequence. After a card is moved from a column leaving a face down card behind, the new card will automatically be flipped over to reveal it. Any Empty column can be filled with a King or pile of cards with a King at the top.

The stock pile contains the remaining cards that have not yet been moved to the foundation or to the tableau areas. Tapping on the top of the stock pile flips and reveals the next card in the deck (flip 1 card or 3 cards at a time depending on the draw option that is selected). Move cards from the stock pile area to either the foundation or to the tableau to continue sequencing cards as long as it is a legal move based on the rules for the tableau. Once all of the cards are flipped over from the stock pile, it can be reset by clicking the empty card slot with the reset arrow icon. In this game mode, the stock pile can be reset as many times as you would like for you to cycle through them again.

Card to Foundation +15 pts|Card from Flip Pile to Tableau +5 pts|Reveal new card on Tableau +5 pts|Reset Stock Pile -15 pts|Every 30 seconds that pass -5 pts|Use an Undo -15 pts|Use a Hint -10 pts|Take a card from the foundation and put it back in play on the Tableau -15 pts|Bonus Points are calculated based on time it took to finish

3 Card Draw - Switch to this mode where every time you tap the top card in the stock pile, 3 cards will be flipped over. You can only access the top card, making this mode more challenging than playing single card mode.| |Left Handed Deal - This option will flip the game orientation so that the stock pile is on the left making the game a little easier to play for left handed players.| |Show Score/Time - This option will hide the top area. Your Score, Time and Moves are still being captured in the background so this can always be shown again in the future.| |All Winning Deals - When this option is selected, all of the new deals can be won. They are not always easy but can be won depending on how the round is played!| |Tap Cards to Move - This game option will remove the ability to tap a card and have it automatically move to a valid location. You will have to press and hold a card you want to move and drag it to the location you want it to go. If the move is not valid, the card will move back to its original location.| |Show Hints - The Hint button at the bottom in the main navigation can be hidden to make the game a little harder.| |Show Undos -  The Undo button at the bottom in the main navigation can be hidden to make the game a little harder.

Each time you win a game (1 Card or 3 Card Draw), your points are added towards a larger goal where you can unlock rewards once the goal is met. Each tier requires a different amount of points to unlock the reward. As an example, if you are 1000/5000 towards your reward, it means you have 1000 points towards the 5000 points target. You must win more games and the score for each winning game will fill the progress bar by that amount, once the points threshold is met, you unlock the reward.
Vegas Solitaire uses a standard 52 card deck of playing cards (without jokers).

The overall goal is to earn more money than is wagered. The player starts with an initial wager of -$52 (-$1 for every card in the deck) and the objective of the game is to reveal and sort cards in the main game area (called the tableau) and move them up into the foundation piles (4 boxes with “A” inside). Once cards are moved to the foundation it will earn the player $. Move all of the cards to the foundation to win a maximum of $208 ($260 less your initial wager of $52).
A. Foundation|B. Tableau|C. Scoring|D. Stock Pile|E. Main Navigation

Cards of the same suit can be placed on top of the Ace in order from Ace to King. Once all 4 foundation piles are built up, the game is over.

The game begins with a cascading arrangement of cards (randomly dealt) being placed in the 7 tableau columns face down with the top card in each column revealed. Card sequences can be built by placing cards in descending values (e.g., J, 10, 9, 8, etc.) and in alternating colors (Red, Black) on top of each other. Within the tableau area, sequences of cards or partially completed piles can be moved on top of other cards in other columns as long as it will continue the descending card sequence. After a card is moved from a column leaving a face down card behind, the new card will automatically be flipped over to reveal it. Any Empty column can be filled with a King or pile of cards with a King at the top.

The stock pile contains the remaining cards that have not yet been moved to the foundation or to the tableau areas. Tapping on the top of the stock pile flips and reveals the next card in the deck (flip 1 card or 3 cards at a time depending on the draw option that is selected). Move cards from the stock pile area to either the foundation or to the tableau to continue sequencing cards as long as it is a legal move based on the rules for the tableau. Once all of the cards are flipped over from the stock pile, the game is over. When the Draw 3 option is on, 3 passes are allowed through the stock pile before the game is over, otherwise only one pass is allowed
Initial wager -$52 (-$1 for every card in the deck)|Cards to the foundation +$5|Foundation back to the Tableau -$5|Hint $0|Undo $0
With the Vegas cumulative option on (in settings), the overall $ value is maintained between games, otherwise if this option is off the starting wager is reset at the start of each new game.

Cumulative Scoring - When this game mode is selected, your overall $ value carries over between games. Each game will cost you $52 to start. How high can build up your $ balance? Each game mode for 1 Card Draw or 3 Card draw will have its own cumulative total. Once this mode is selected, a new option will appear to allow you to reset your cumulative total.| |Reset Cumulative - Pressing this option will reset your game $ to 0 and redeal a new game (which costs you $52) so you will begin again with a balance of -$52.| |3 Card Draw - Switch to this mode where every time you tap the top card in the stock pile, 3 cards will be flipped over. You can only access the top card, making this mode more challenging than playing single card mode. Each day, a new challenge is available to play. The challenge will be a standard Classic Solitaire 1 card game format. Each of the daily challenges are winnable but at times may require a certain sequence of moves to be played in order to win (If you get stuck, you are able to replay the game to try again or quit if you can’t figure it out). You can only finish the daily challenge once a day and will have to wait for the following day to play again.
Scoring will follow the same scoring structure as the Classic Solitaire game.

If you can solve the challenge, you will be awarded your daily progress. Daily challenges do not have to be completed every single day as each completed day will move your overall progress forward by 1 (If you miss a daily challenge, your progress will not be reset. The next day, you can pick up where you left off). Once you reach one of the thresholds (5, 10 and 15 Daily Challenges Complete, you are awarded a larger prize). After you have completed 15 daily challenges, the progress bar will be reset the next day you return and you can complete the 15 day challenge again.

Each time you win a daily challenge, you will earn 1 day of progress towards a reward. You can only add progress towards the reward once each day. As an example, if you are 1/15 towards your reward, it means you have successfully completed 1 daily challenge towards the end target of completing 15 daily challenges. In this case you must win more daily challenges to fill the progress bar, if a smaller threshold is met along the way to the larger goal, you will unlock a reward.

After you complete a Daily Challenge, you are able to share that score from the results screen or the Daily Challenge recap screen up until the next day’s challenge starts (indicated by the red timer).
Tapping the top card of the stock pile will flip it over.
Tapping the reset icon “arrow” in the stock pile area will reset the remaining stock pile cards.
Moving Cards by Pressing and Dragging

Press and hold to drag cards from one position to another and then release the card(s) to drop it. The card(s) will automatically lock into the closest legal position or be returned to the original position if a legal move cannot be made). Drag an entire stack of cards or only a portion of the stack by pressing in the middle of a stack to drag only some of the cards to a new column.

Tap a card to automatically move it to a location without dragging it (it will move to the new legal position where it could move). If there are multiple legal locations for the card to move to, the system will randomly select one of the new legal positions.

If you cannot continue or want to restart the current game, click the main navigation icon “Card icon with the +” to restart your current game with a brand-new shuffle. You will lose your current progress in the game you are in.

If there is a possible move to make, click the main navigation hint icon which will be visible and can be pressed to automatically move one of the cards in your game. If there are no legal moves for you to make, the button will be semi-transparent and inactive. Using hints will decrease your score.

After moving a card at any point in the game, the undo button in the main navigation will revert the card positions to their positions before the last move. Tapping the undo multiple times will continue to revert the game to earlier states.
To change the game type, tap settings and scroll to “Game Options” and press the name of the game type you wish to play (Standard or Vegas) and select the desired options for that game variation.
